text: Martinez is a city in and the county seat of Contra Costa County, California, in the East Bay of the San Francisco Bay Area. The population was 37,287 at the 2020 census. The downtown has many old buildings and antique shops. It is on the south shore of the Carquinez Strait in the San Francisco Bay Area. ==References== Category:Cities in California Category:Cities in the San Francisco Bay Area Category:County seats in California Category:Settlements in Contra Costa County, California
